A pedestrian has been taken to hospital after she was hit by a car in a Leicestershire town. Police said officers were called to Leicester Road, in Oadby, at about 13:00 BST on Monday.The force said East Midlands Ambulance Service was also in attendance and the  woman's injuries were not reported to be life-threatening. No-one else was injured in the crash, police said.
Officers said the road was not closed but there was a build-up of traffic, and asked drivers to take an alternative route. Follow BBC Leicester on Facebook, on X, or on Instagram. Send your story ideas to eastmidsnews@bbc.co.uk or via WhatsApp on 0808 100 2210.
